<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Atlanta Woman Picks Final Four  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Here's what Kristin Helgeson gets for four lucky
guesses: high-fives from women for one-upping the guys and marriage
proposals from men who love basketball.
</P>
<P>
   The 29-year-old Atlanta graphics designer was the only person
out of 590,000 to predict each of the Final Four teams in a contest
by ESPN.com. She says she's not a huge sports fan and prefers
football and hockey to basketball.
</P>
<P>
   When the Web site reported her feat -- and posted a link to her
e-mail address -- Helgeson received hundreds of messages. Some
wanted help picking stocks or lottery numbers. One said, ''You're a
goddess.''
</P>
<P>
   ''There were a few where the subject says, 'Will you marry me?'
Some ask for a picture. ... A few women have written: 'Who says
women don't know anything about basketball? You show em! Way to go,
girl!''' Helgeson said.
</P>
<P>
   It was not immediately clear if Helgeson will get any prize for
correctly picking the four teams since she did not accurately
predict the championship matchup.
</P>
<P>
   Helgeson entered the contest because five guys in her office
were doing it. She rushed through her picks before leaving the
country for two weeks. She didn't watch any tournament games until
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Helgeson says, ''Mostly, people are just curious: 'It's killing
me. How did you do it?'''
</P>
<P>
   She picked Florida because she's an alumna. Wisconsin was where
her father went to school. She has a friend who went to North
Carolina. She picked Michigan State out of sympathy, after watching
them play Florida in the Citrus Bowl. The Spartans won 37-34.
</P>
<P>
   ''I thought we were bad sports against them,'' she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
