<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Rattles Taiwan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) -- A moderate earthquake struck near a lake
resort today in central Taiwan, seismologists said. No damage or
injuries were immediately reported.
</P>
<P>
   The 4.3-magnitude quake hit 10 miles west of Sun Moon Lake, the
island's largest natural lake, the Central Weather Bureau said.
</P>
<P>
   The resort area suffered severe damage when a 7.6-magnitude
tremor jolted Taiwan on Sept. 21. Lakefront hotels collapsed and
several landmark structures were ruined.
</P>
<P>
   Since the big quake, which killed 2,400 people, more than 12,000
aftershocks and tremors have rattled Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
   Located along the earthquake-prone Pacific Rim and crisscrossed
by 51 fault lines, scores of earthquakes hit Taiwan each year.
</P>
</TEXT>
