<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Sinks 227; Dow Up 33  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Technology shares plunged at the start of
trading today, with Microsoft weighing down the Nasdaq composite
index. But rising financial shares kept the Dow Jones industrials
in positive territory.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq composite index was down 227.54, or by almost 5
percent, at 4,345.29.
</P>
<P>
   Microsoft fell 12 5/16 to 93 15/16 as the company appeared
poised for harsh penalties in its antitrust case. Microsoft's
negotiations with the government broke down on Saturday, and U.S.
District Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson is expected to rule any day
on Microsoft's guilt.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 33.82 at 10,955.74.
</P>
<P>
   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was down 9.71 to 1,488.87.
</P>
<P>
   Microsoft wasn't the only software company suffering today.
Legato Systems, a maker of storage software, lost nearly half of
its value, tumbling 22 1/64 to 22 39/64. The company told the
Securities and Exchange Commission late Friday that it would delay
the filing of its annual 10-K form, raising concerns that the
company would restate some financial results.
</P>
<P>
   Even though Microsoft is a component of the Dow, Wall Street's
best-known indicator gained on the strength of financial stocks.
American Express rose 4\ to 153 3/16, and J.P. Morgan rose 3 11/16
to 135 7/16.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 7-to-5 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 116.15 million shares
in the early going, well behind Friday's early pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 3.34 to 535.75.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average rose 2.0 percent to a new
3-year high, despite the hospitalization of the prime minister and
the appointment of an acting premier. In afternoon trading,
Germany's Xetra DAX index was down 1.5 percent, and France's CAC-40
was down 2.0 percent. Britain's FT-SE 100 was up 1.0 percent. A
computer problem at the London Stock Exchange made it impossible to
calculate the main market index for more than four hours in early
trading.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
