<HEADLINE> CNNfn Expanding Programming Day  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- CNNfn is expanding its business.
</P>
<P>
   The CNN sister network will boost its business-news programming
to 24 hours Monday through Friday beginning in June, the network
announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ''With around-the-clock programming and our upcoming expansion
to the West Coast, CNNfn is uniquely positioned to cover the new
economy, the global economy and to meet the needs of prime-time
viewers in Western time zones,'' said Shelby Coffey III, president
of CNN Business News and CNNfn.
</P>
<P>
   CNNfn currently airs weekdays from 6 a.m. to midnight Eastern
time.
</P>
<P>
   The network previously announced that CNN's flagship business
program, ''Moneyline,'' will become bi-coastal in September when
Willow Bay begins co-anchoring the program from Los Angeles, with
Stuart Varney remaining in New York.
</P>
<P>
   Launched in 1995, CNNfn is available in roughly 13.3 million
homes. Its chief competitor, CNBC, signed on in 1989 and is
available in 72 million homes.
</P>
