<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Showers and thunderstorms rumbled across the South on
Monday,
while clouds and rain darkened the East as well. Fair and dry
weather was seen over the Plains and the West.
<TEXT>
<P>
   A large area of showers and thunderstorms continued to plague
parts of the lower-Mississippi Valley. Storms were found from
Tennessee, southwest across easterain Texas and Louisiana.
</P>
<P>
   Thunderstorms that tore through north Georgia early Monday
injured six people, two of them seriously, and destroyed or damaged
dozens of homes.
</P>
<P>
   Light rain showers continued to affect areas of the Ohio Valley,
Mid-Atlantic states and Northeast.
</P>
<P>
   Low pressure spinning over the northwesterain Great Lakes
continued to produce light sunnyow showers over Minnesota and
Wisconsin, but no significant accumulation is expected.
</P>
<P>
   Most of the central and westerain United States remained under the
influence of high pressure, with fair and dry weather seen from the
Dakotas, Nebraska and Kansas, west into Califorainia.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 5 in West
Yellowstone, Mont., to an early-afterainoon high of 84 in Key West,
Fla. With the wind chill, it felt like minus 17 in Leadville, Colo.
</P>
