<HEADLINE> Colombian Prosecutor Slain  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) -- A gunman on a motorcycle shot and killed
a federal prosecutor as she stepped outside her home in Medellin on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The motorcycle driven by an accomplice sped away and there were
no arrests made, said police, who didn't specify a possible motive.
</P>
<P>
   The slain attorney, 32-year-old Margarita Pulgarin, belonged to
a corps of special prosecutors working on sensitive drug
trafficking and terrorism cases.
</P>
<P>
   The prosecutors had worked anonymously for their protection
until their identities and those of many judges were made public
following complaints that defendants were denied due process by the
so-called ''faceless'' justice system.
</P>
<P>
   Pulgarin was the second prosecutor from Antioquia State
assassinated since the reform, said a statement Monday by her
fellow state prosecutors.
</P>
<P>
   Seven others have fled the country amid threats, said the
colleagues. They threatened to massively resign or flee the country
if the government did not provide greater security.
</P>
</TEXT>
