<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Seagate Technology Inc., down 8{ at 53
</P>
<P>
   More than a dozen shareholder suits have been filed to block the
planned sale of Seagate, The Wall Street Journal reported. The
suits, filed in Delaware Chancery Court, contend that the buyout
price for Seagate -- nearly $20 billion -- is inadequate. Last week,
Seagate said it would be taken private in a two-step deal with
Veritas Software and a buyout group led by Silver Lake Partners.
</P>
<P>
American National Can, up 4 1/16 at 17 3/16
</P>
<P>
   London-based Rexam has agreed to buy American National Can, the
world's second-largest producer of aluminum beverage cans, for $2.1
billion. Rexam is paying 18 per share for American National Can,
well above Friday's closing price of 13[ per share.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Challenge Ltd., up 4\ at 11\
</P>
<P>
   Norske Skog ASA, an international pulp and paper group, is
buying Fletcher's paper division for about $2.5 billion. The
purchase includes Fletcher's pulp and paper operations in
Australia, New Zealand, Asia, South America and Canada.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Microsoft Corp., down 15] at 90~
</P>
<P>
   Settlement talks in the government's antitrust case against
Microsoft broke down over the weekend, and a federal judge was
expected to deliver his verdict after the close of trading today.
Analysts say Microsoft faces a harsh penalty and a lengthy appeals
process.
</P>
<P>
Legato Systems Inc., down 24} at 19~
</P>
<P>
   The company, a developer of storage software, said it may have
to restate certain financial results and will delay filing its 10-K
form with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Legato said some
of its sales force had acted outside their authority, entering into
side deals worth about $7 million in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
Starbucks Corp., down 3] at 41 7/16
</P>
<P>
   Lehman Brothers and Merrill Lynch both downgraded the stock.
Lehman Brothers said the company's share price has already risen as
much as its profit outlook justifies.
</P>
<P>
Funco Inc., up 5 at 16~
</P>
<P>
   Electronics Boutique Holdings Corp. plans to acquire Funco for
$110 million, or $17.50 a share, in a deal that combines two video
game retailers. Funco's 400 stores are located primarily in strip
malls.
</P>
</TEXT>
