<HEADLINE> Independent Counsel Hires 2 Lawyers  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Independent Counsel Robert Ray announced
Monday he is hiring two federal prosecutors from Tampa, Fla., in
the investigation of President Clinton and the first lady.
</P>
<P>
   Joining Ray's office are Latour Lafferty, an assistant U.S.
attorney who has handled organized crime cases, and Monte
Richardson, who prosecuted complex fraud cases before becoming
executive assistant U.S. attorney for special projects
community-related programs in the federal prosecutor's office in
Tampa.
</P>
<P>
   Ray has said he is adding staffers to help him determine whether
to file criminal charges against Clinton in the Monica Lewinsky
scandal. Clinton was found in civil contempt by a federal judge for
denying a sexual relationship with the former White House intern
and for testifying that he couldn't recall being alone with her.
Ray's office also is compiling final reports on the six-year
criminal investigation of the president and first lady.
</P>
</TEXT>
