<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air Bag Crushes Boy, 9, to Death  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOURNE, Mass. (AP) -- After his grandmother let him take the
wheel, a 9-year-old boy crashed a car into an embankment of her
driveway and was crushed to death when the air bag inflated.
</P>
<P>
   Joseph A. Pagliarani III was driving his grandmother's 1995
Mercury sedan in her driveway Sunday night, police Sgt. Joel Gould
said.
</P>
<P>
   After returning from a trip for ice cream, the boy's
grandmother, Shirley Pagliarani, 71, allowed the boy to drive the
approximately 140-foot stretch of her driveway, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Neither the boy nor the grandmother were wearing seat belts, and
Gould said it wasn't clear if a restraint could have saved the
child's life.
</P>
<P>
   Pagliarani was ''very shook up and upset'' and was not charged
in connection with the accident, Gould said. It is not illegal for
an adult to allow a child to drive on private property.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
