<DOCNO> APW20000403.0249 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-03 22:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NY's Williams To DH; Sore Triceps  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Gold Glove center fielder Bernie Williams
will be used as the DH by the New York Yankees until his sore right
triceps muscle feels better, manager Joe Torre said.
</P>
<P>
   Ricky Ledee started Monday night's opener against the Anaheim
Angels in center with Shane Spencer in left.
</P>
<P>
   ''It isn't the type of thing that's going to get worse, but I
don't want him in a situation where he is going to have to throw
somebody out,'' Torre said.
</P>
<P>
   Williams had been icing his right shoulder much of the spring
because of what he said was a tired arm, but the new problem is
unrelated, Torre said.
</P>
<P>
   The triceps has been bothering Williams for about a week, and he
sat out the Yankees' final exhibition game Saturday in San
Francisco.
</P>
</TEXT>
