<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mighty Ducks Sign Andy McDonald  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- The Anaheim Mighty Ducks agreed to terms
Monday with free-agent forward Andy McDonald, a finalist for the
Hobey Baker Award as the nation's top collegiate player.
</P>
<P>
   McDonald, a 22-year-old center from Colgate University, had 25
goals and 33 assists in 34 games as a senior. He was selected as
Eastern College Athletic Conference Player of the year.
</P>
<P>
   In his four seasons at Colgate, McDonald scored 67 goals and
added 88 assists in 137 games.
</P>
<P>
   If McDonald is the Hobey Baker winner, he would become the
fourth current member of the Ducks to be selected, joining Paul
Kariya, Kip Miller and Tony Hrkac.
</P>
<P>
   The voting will be announced on Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
